<h1>Versions</h1>
<h3>Version <%= String.new(ScholarSphere::Application::config.scholarsphere_version).sub "v", "" %> (<%= ScholarSphere::Application::config.scholarsphere_release_date %>)</h3>
<p>
<ul>
  <li>Adding pagination on collection show and edit pages</li>
  <li>Displaying file permissions on the generic file show page</li>
  <li>Changed resource type "Master's Thesis" to "Thesis" on the Descriptions (metadata) template.</li>
</ul>
</p>
<h3>Version 1.9 (February 13, 2014)</h3>
<p>
<ul>
  <li>Fixed bugs with Facets not displaying in Safari</li>
  <li>Added validation to Collections to require a Title</li>
  <li>Included query links on GenericFile Show page</li>
  <li>Fixed user profile page to display the correct number of deposited files</li>
  <li>Made highlighted files easier to remove and thus manage</li>
  <li>Added relative date to notifications page</li>
</ul>
</p>
<h3>Version 1.8 (November 26, 2013)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Enhancements to the deployment process.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<h3>Version 1.7 (July 9, 2013)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Users can upload files on behalf of other users for approval.</li>
    <li>Users can designate others to be authorized to upload files for them to by pass a case-by-case authorization process.</li>
    <li>Files that have been uploaded to ScholarSphere can be logically arranged into collections.</li>
    <li>Users can authenticate to their Dropbox account from the ScholarSphere upload screen and import files into ScholarSphere.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<h3>Version 1.6 (May 29, 2013)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Users can transfer ownership of files to other users.</li>
    <li>Performance enhancements.</li>
    <li>Highlighted files on user profile page display thumbnail images.</li>
    <li>Dashboard actions arranged into dropdown list.</li>
    <li>Users receive email confirmation of contact form submission.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h3>Version 1.5 (Apr 30, 2013)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Maximum size for an individual file raised to 500MB.</li>
    <li>Maximum size for a total upload raised to 1GB.</li>
    <li>Walkthrough videos added to help page.</li>
    <li>Titles of uploaded files now appear in the browser's titlebar.</li>
    <li>List of following/follower users on user profiles enhanced.</li>
    <li>Unicode characters pasted into metadata fields no longer break batch updates.</li>
    <li>Site administrators may now view usage statistics.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h3>Version 1.4 (Mar 13, 2013)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full-text indexing and searching.</li>
    <li>Removed Google+ accounts from user profiles.</li>
    <li>Added LinkedIn accounts to user profiles.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h3>Version 1.3 (Dec 18,2012)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>ScholarSphere version is in the footer (linked to new features).</li>
    <li>Users have the ability to make their social accounts visible from their profile page in ScholarSphere.</li>
    <li>Users have access to the list of users in the ScholarSphere system by clicking the View Users button from their profile page.</li>
    <li>Users can highlight up to five files from their dashboard, and have them display on their profile page.</li>
    <li>Single-use links are available from the dashboard.</li>
   </ul>
</p>

<h3>Version 1.2 (Nov 7, 2012)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Added batch edit and delete.</li>
    <li>Notifications are pushed automatically, and no longer require page refresh.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h3>Version 1.1 (Sept 24, 2012)</h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Moved batch processing for metadata to background processing to speed uploads.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

<h3>Version 1.0 (Sept 11, 2012) </h3>
<p>
  <ul>
    <li>Initial release of ScholarSphere.</li>
  </ul>
</p>

